In addition, the amount of data to be processed becomes increasing to the point that in the last five years more versions, variations and engineizations have come on the market than in the past fifteen years.
Once a new car gets on the market, business starts work.
It is a difficult task, because each one of the thousand parts of the vehicle must be catagolized and its price must be entered.
In addition, each model creates a "intelligent" graphic image on which you can "click" different parts of the vehicle.
If this is a highly sold model, work can be completed in one week if the procedure is rapidly ahead.
If this is a less usual car, it may take up to three or four months. Currently Audatex has 99.2% of the cars distributed in Spain with complete information.
For example, among the exclusive models they have information about the Porsche models, but not about Ferrari or Lamborghini.
With regard to the road car park, it is more than 99%.
